  "text": "GFP was detected only in grafts containing cultured Sox2 þ cells (Figure 6e-j) , indicating that Sox2 expression was not induced in Sox2À cells on grafting. CD133ÀSox2À and CD133 þ Sox2À cultured cells were largely confined to the DP (Figure 6k and l) . In contrast, CD133 þ Sox2 þ cells were found both within the DP and throughout the dermis (Figure 6m ; [CITATION_1] . The ratio of awl/auchene to ZZ hairs was the same in all grafts (Figure 6o) , and cultured Sox2 þ CD133 þ and Sox2ÀCD133 þ cells contributed to both hair types. This indicates that the presence of a Sox2 þ sphere within a DP does not inhibit ZZ hair formation.",
